<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="40" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="40">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="40">
One of the few species of the genus restricted to conifers. Distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Xyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xyleborus" order="Lecanorales" pageId="21" pageNumber="40" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Xyleborus</taxonomicName>
by the steep declivity which occupies the apical 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Â¼">1/4</normalizedToken>
of the elytra, and broadly rounded posterolateral margin of the declivity. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. pubescens" pageId="21" pageNumber="40" rank="species" species="pubescens">X. pubescens</taxonomicName>
by the larger declivital denticles and smaller, deeply impressed declivital strial punctures.
</paragraph>
